title: Cotangent formula for the rotation of a triangle edge
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Let $$p_0,p_1,p_2$$ be a positively oriented non-degenerate triangle in the plane with edge vectors $$e_i = p_{i+1} - p_i$$ and interior angles $$\alpha_i$$ at $$p_i$$ and let $$J$$ denote the positive 90&deg;-rotation. Then
$$
Je_0 = \cot\alpha_1\; e_1 - \cot\alpha_2\; e_2.
$$